Stephanie says:
i just made it a million times less funny

the earth spits vitriol and fire from the stony abyss of a furnace, the belly of the land
the burning black mass makes fertile the ground
the ashes of death bear forth life
so I learn that from chaos and uncertainty
from violence
from destruction
there is growth, there is hope, there is creation
and the God of all things, who sees land made from fire and green sprouts from gray cinders
will make new in me an abundant land and a sturdy tree
in whose branches He will rest and reign King.



Then shall all shackles fall; the stormy clangor
Of wild war music o’er the earth shall cease;
Love shall tread out the baleful fire of anger,
And in its ashes plant the tree of peace.

John G. Whittier
